Previously they also had a Paraclete, to be sure the Lord himself abiding with them in the flesh: by both the sweetness of whose miracles and the might of his preaching they were accustomed to be raised up and encouraged, so that they could not be scandalized at persecution by unbelievers.

To be sure because after his resurrection, ascending into heaven he had forsaken them bodily, to whom the presence of his divine majesty was yet never absent: rightly he added concerning this Paraclete, that is the Holy Spirit, "And I will pray my Father, and he shall give you another Comforter, that he may abide with you forever."

